**FULL URL**: [http://api.adempiere.io/](http://api.adempiere.io/api)dictionary/browsers/{id}

**Method**: GET

**Parameters (Params):**

- id (Int32, Mandatory)
    

**Application Example**

``` bash
curl --location 'http://api.adempiere.io/dictionary/browsers/50000' \
--header 'Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJqdGkiOiIxMDAwMTQ5IiwiQURfQ2xpZW50X0lEIjoxMSwiQURfT3JnX0lEIjowLCJBRF9Sb2xlX0lEIjoxMDIsIkFEX1VzZXJfSUQiOjEwMCwiTV9XYXJlaG91c2VfSUQiOjAsIkFEX0xhbmd1YWdlIjoiZW5fVVMiLCJpYXQiOjE3MTA1MTA0MDEsImV4cCI6MTcxMDU5NjgwMX0.nYQbrcT9RyHNRCf-oNM50ZVSO6uJ9gvrQQ7e0fzU9Ik'

 ```

**Example Answer:**

``` json
{
    "id": 50000,
    "value": "SalesOrderToPicking",
    "name": "Salas Order to Picking",
    "description": "This Smart Browse allow select the Sales Order to generate an Outbound Order.",
    "help": "",
    "access_level": 3,
    "context_column_names": [],
    "is_updateable": false,
    "is_deleteable": false,
    "is_selected_by_default": false,
    "is_collapsible_by_default": true,
    "is_executed_query_by_default": false,
    "is_show_total": true,
    "view_id": 50000,
    "window": {
        "id": 143,
        "name": "Sales Order",
        "description": "Enter and change sales orders",
        "help": "The Order Window allows you to enter and modify Sales Orders.  ",
        "is_active": true,
        "is_sales_transaction": true,
        "window_type": "T",
        "context_info": {
            "id": 50000,
            "name": "Order Status",
            "description": "Used for show a Status of Order",
            "message_text": {
                "id": 377,
                "value": "OrderSummary",
                "message_type": "",
                "message_text": "{0} Line(s) - {1,number,#,##0.00} -  Total: {2,number,#,##0.00}  {3}  =  {4,number,#,##0.00}",
                "message_tip": "",
                "is_active": false,
                "uuid": ""
            },
            "sql_statement": "SELECT COUNT(*) AS Lines, o.TotalLines, o.GrandTotal, c.ISO_Code,  currencyBase(o.GrandTotal,o.C_Currency_ID,o.DateAcct, o.AD_Client_ID,o.AD_Org_ID) AS ConvAmt \nFROM C_Order o \nINNER JOIN C_Currency c ON (o.C_Currency_ID=c.C_Currency_ID) \nINNER JOIN C_OrderLine l ON (o.C_Order_ID=l.C_Order_ID) \nWHERE o.C_Order_ID=@C_Order_ID@\nGROUP BY o.C_Currency_ID, c.ISO_Code, o.TotalLines, o.GrandTotal, o.DateAcct, o.AD_Client_ID, o.AD_Org_ID",
            "is_active": false,
            "uuid": "8cb3c434-fb40-11e8-a479-7a0060f0aa01"
        },
        "tabs": [],
        "uuid": "a52203d2-fb40-11e8-a479-7a0060f0aa01"
    },
    "process": {
        "uuid": "a42caeb4-fb40-11e8-a479-7a0060f0aa01",
        "id": 53186,
        "value": "WM_InOutbound Generate",
        "name": "Generare Outbound Order",
        "description": "This process allows to generate a new document as the result of gathering Sales Orders, Manufacture Orders, Distribution Orders based on several criteria such as :",
        "help": "Warehouse, Order, Document Type, Promised Date range, Ordered Dates, Business Partner, Country, Zip Code, Product and Shipper, these parameters can be configured leveraging the Smart Browse artifact.\n\nThus, it is required to previously define those parameters to be used in orther to determine wich products are to be included in the Picking Orders, these paraneters are:\n\n*Area Type\n*Section type\n*Overwrite Delivery Rule\n*Generate Picking List\n*Print Picking List\n*Stand-by Location\n*Document Status for the Picking Order",
        "is_report": false,
        "show_help": "Y",
        "workflow_id": 0,
        "form_id": 0,
        "browser_id": 0,
        "report_view_id": 0,
        "print_format_id": 0,
        "report_export_types": [],
        "has_parameters": true,
        "parameters": []
    }
}

 ```

**Common mistakes:**

- id does not correspond to any query

``` json
    "code": 13,
    "message": "Smart Browse * Not found *",
    "details": []
}

 ```

| 1.0 | 15/03/2024 | Ricardo | Initial creation of the document. |
